[I] A C++ XML parser

[T] Xerces C++ is a validating XML parser written in a portable subset of
[T] C++. It makes it easy to give your application the ability to read and
[T] write XML data. A shared library is provided for parsing, generating,
[T] manipulating, and validating XML documents. It is faithful to the XML
[T] 1. 0 recommendation and associated standards (DOM 1. 0, DOM 2. 0. SAX
[T] 1. 0, SAX 2. 0, Namespaces). It also provides an implementation of a
[T] subset of the Schema.

[U] https://xml.apache.org/xerces-c/

[A] The Apache foundation <xerces-c-dev@xml.apache.org>
[M] The T2 Project <t2@t2-project.org>

